snippet.textDisplay:
It's originally a sambalpuri song, a dialect of Odia language spoken in western odisha but some of its words have been changed by these singers, also they are not keeping the cultural heritage which is they are singing the song without the permission of the original sambalpuri singers😢. Still they worked hard and made a nice version of Rangabati in Coke studio❤😊 but people should also know about its original origination of language as it is our cultural heritage which is the sambalpuri language spoken in Western Odisha.
JAI MAA SAMLEI🙏
JAI JAGANNATH 🙏
BANDE UTKALA JANANI🙏
snippet.textOriginal:
It's originally a sambalpuri song, a dialect of Odia language spoken in western odisha but some of its words have been changed by these singers, also they are not keeping the cultural heritage which is they are singing the song without the permission of the original sambalpuri singers😢. Still they worked hard and made a nice version of Rangabati in Coke studio❤😊 but people should also know about its original origination of language as it is our cultural heritage which is the sambalpuri language spoken in Western Odisha.
JAI MAA SAMLEI🙏
JAI JAGANNATH 🙏
BANDE UTKALA JANANI🙏
